The National Working Committee of the All Progressives Congress has named former Governor of Oyo State, and Deputy National Chairman of the party as acting National Chairman. The decision of the APC NWC followed the ruling of the Appeal Court upholding the suspension of Oshiomhole as National Chairman. A statement by the National Publicity Secretary OF APC, Lanre Issa-Onilu, said, “The National Working Committee of the All Progressives Congress has received the news indicating the Appeal Court has upheld the suspension of the Party’s National Chairman, Comrade Adams Oshiomhole by an FCT High Court pending the determination of the substantive suit. “Guided by advice from the Party’s legal department in line with the provisions of Section 14.2. (iii) of the Party’s constitution, the Deputy National Chairman (South), Sen. Abiola Ajimobi will serve as the Party’s Acting National Chairman. “According to Section 14.2. (iii), of the APC constitution, the Deputy National Chairman, North/South “Shall act as the National Chairman in the absence of the National Chairman from his zone”. 